The dataset includes data from  in vitro  experiments on 11 cell lines: V79-379A, V79-753B, DLD1, SQ20B, CI-1, C3H10T1/2, SCC25, HCT116, H184B5 F5-1M/10 and HF19 (folder &bdquo;data&rdquo;). These data were taken from the survival curves available in the source articles and then a linear-quadratic model was fitted to them , from which the &alpha; and &beta; parameters were obtained (04_Distributions, Figure 1). All operations on the experimental data, their reading,&nbsp; preparation(01_PreaparingData.ipynb) and&nbsp;analysis (02_Fitting_LQmodel.ipynb) were performed in Jupyter Notebooks.&nbsp; &nbsp;The experimental database has been cleared of outliers based on several conditions(03_Outliers.ipynb). 

A comparison of biological dose (05_SOBP.ipynb , Figure 2) was set up on a depth-dose and LET profile (&bdquo;data/sobp_10mln&rdquo;) as being used in radiobiological  in vivo  mouse experiments (folder &bdquo;mc_simulation&rdquo;). 

