Bunshi is a Geant4 application designed to estimate and assess dose in hospital proton therapy bunker facilities. 
The dose estimation is based on the simulation of secondary radiation generation at localized points of the beamline, from the estimated primary proton losses at these points. This information must be provided by the accelerator manufacturer, although it could also be extracted by Monte Carlo simulations. The simulations are post-processed to obtain the expected annual doses that are estimated from the planned annual workload at the facility. The dose rates can also be evaluated from the required intensity at the isocenter. 
